cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for action anticipation, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the use of a reinforcement module for sequence-level supervision suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques and the focus on performance evaluation suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The application of these techniques to robotics and surveillance suggests that it may also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the use of video datasets and the focus on human interactions suggests that it may also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
